[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":247},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2025\u002F04\u002F24\u002Fvscode-cannot-find-git-set-git-path\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2025\u002F04\u002F24\u002Fvscode-cannot-find-git-set-git-path\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2025\u002F04\u002F24\u002Fvscode-cannot-find-git-set-git-path\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2025\u002F04\u002F24\u002Fvscode-cannot-find-git-set-git-path\u002F":223,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fvscode\u002F2025\u002F04\u002F24\u002Fvscode-cannot-find-git-set-git-path\u002F":232},"\u002Fvscode\u002F20250424\u002F4258825567\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":206,"date":207,"description":208,"extension":209,"lang":210,"meta":211,"navigation":212,"path":213,"readingMinutes":214,"seo":215,"standalone":216,"stem":217,"tags":218,"tldr":220,"updated":207,"url":221,"__hash__":222},"content\u002Fen\u002FVSCode\u002Fvscode-cannot-find-git-set-git-path.md","VSCode 'Can't Find Git, Install It or Use git.path' — How to Fix","5595968622",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":200},"minimark",[11,16,25,29,32,48,55,58,62,65,73,76,82,89,94,97,109,115,132,135,152,155,193,196],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19,20,24],"p",{},"One day I opened VSCode to start coding and got hit with \"Can't find Git. Install it or use the ",[21,22,23],"code",{},"git.path"," setting to specify the Git path.\" So here's the fix.",[12,26,28],{"id":27},"what-happened","What happened",[17,30,31],{},"I hadn't opened VSCode in a while, and the moment I did, this popup showed up:",[33,34,39],"pre",{"className":35,"code":36,"language":37,"meta":38,"style":38},"language-txt shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","Can't find Git. Install it or use the \"git.path\" setting to specify the Git path.\n","txt","",[21,40,41],{"__ignoreMap":38},[42,43,46],"span",{"class":44,"line":45},"line",1,[42,47,36],{},[17,49,50],{},[51,52],"img",{"alt":53,"src":54},"Can't find Git error","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fvscode-git-path\u002F20250424094928.png",[17,56,57],{},"So, fix incoming.",[12,59,61],{"id":60},"the-fix","The fix",[17,63,64],{},"First sanity check: do you have Git installed on your machine at all? If not, install it and you're done.",[17,66,67,68,72],{},"But in my case Git ",[69,70,71],"em",{},"was"," already installed, so I had to handle this manually. For context, my VSCode was version 1.99.3. I'm guessing some update broke VSCode's automatic Git path detection, so we need to set it explicitly.",[17,74,75],{},"Open VSCode settings.",[17,77,78],{},[51,79],{"alt":80,"src":81},"Settings","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fvscode-git-path\u002F20250424095708.png",[17,83,84,85,88],{},"Switch to ",[21,86,87],{},"settings.json",".",[17,90,91],{},[51,92],{"alt":87,"src":93},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fother\u002Fvscode-git-path\u002F20250424095831.png",[17,95,96],{},"Search for:",[33,98,102],{"className":99,"code":100,"language":101,"meta":38,"style":38},"language-json shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","\"git.path\"\n","json",[21,103,104],{"__ignoreMap":38},[42,105,106],{"class":44,"line":45},[42,107,100],{"class":108},"sTRMh",[17,110,111,112,114],{},"If you don't find it (same as me), add this line to ",[21,113,87],{}," manually:",[33,116,118],{"className":99,"code":117,"language":101,"meta":38,"style":38},"\"git.path\": \"your Git install path\"\n",[21,119,120],{"__ignoreMap":38},[42,121,122,125,129],{"class":44,"line":45},[42,123,124],{"class":108},"\"git.path\"",[42,126,128],{"class":127},"sMAXC",": ",[42,130,131],{"class":108},"\"your Git install path\"\n",[17,133,134],{},"On my Mac, Git lives at:",[33,136,138],{"className":99,"code":137,"language":101,"meta":38,"style":38},"\"git.path\": \"\u002Fusr\u002Flocal\u002Fbin\u002Fgit\",\n",[21,139,140],{"__ignoreMap":38},[42,141,142,144,146,149],{"class":44,"line":4